        "details": {
            "description": "<p>Daemonic curses slither and crawl through malevolent runes carved in four stone pillars. HP is per-pillar.</p>",
            "disable": "<p><span data-pf2-check=\"thievery\" data-pf2-label=\"Disable Thievery DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"21\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Thievery</span> (trained) to scratch out a pillar's runes, <em>@Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.Dispel Magic]{Dispel Magic}</em> (2nd level; counteract DC 18) to counteract a pillar's magic, or <span data-pf2-check=\"athletics\" data-pf2-traits=\"action:force-open\" data-pf2-label=\"Disable Athletics DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"21\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Athletics (Force Open)</span> to push a pillar over. Disabling a pillar requires two actions. Disabling all four pillars or slaying Sezruth disables the trap</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 3
            },
            "reset": "",
            "routine": "<p><strong>Routine (4 actions):</strong> The trap loses 1 action each turn for each disabled pillar. On its initiative, the trap uses each action to afflict a different non-evil creature in the room with thirst. The creature must attempt a <span data-pf2-saving-throw=\"fortitude\" data-pf2-traits=\"damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Foretold Ruin DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"20\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Fortitude save</span>.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success:</strong> The creature is temporarily immune to additional negative effects from the foretold ruin hazard's reaction for 24 hours. The hazard has no awareness of this immunity and continues to target this creature.</p>\n<p><strong>Success:</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure:</strong> The creature is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Fatigued]{Fatigued} until they drink water. If the creature was already fatigued, they take [[/r 1d6 #nonlethal mental]]{1d6 nonlethal mental damage}.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> The creature is fatigued until they drink water and takes [[/r 1d6 #nonlethal mental]]{1d6 nonlethal mental damage}. If the creature was already fatigued, they instead take [[/r 2d6 #nonlethal mental]]{2d6 nonlethal mental damage}.</p>"
        },
